      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IMA CHARMA (3) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 3 metres from the winner in fourth over 2100m at Charlton. Has the benefit of a good draw. Tackles a similar assignment and he can take care of this line-up. ILLAWONG PHOENIX (1) is in good form at present. Finished third at her latest appearance over 1690m at Maryborough, beaten 6 metres. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Tackles a similar assignment and she can grab that well-deserved win. DOUGS TRIBE (4) finished fifth two runs ago then broke and finished a distant tenth over 1720m at Melton at the latest appearance. Won't find this any harder and he can bounce back to top-three form.. HAVADASH JOH (5) is the next elect off a last-start win by a neck at this track over 2180m.",
